    <xhtml name="long">It is necessary to calculate the pairwise distances between all elements.<br/>
<br/>
<span style="text-decoration:underline"><b>There are routines for agglomerative clustering:</b></span><br/>
<i>(1) average linkage:</i> it will be the mean of the distances of the joining clusters weighted by the number of elements each cluster holds. Disadvantages: Average-link clustering may cause elongated clusters to split and for portions of neighboring elongated clusters to merge.<br/>
<i>(2) centroid linkage:</i> each cluster is defined by its centroid: a data point that represents all the points included in the cluster. </xhtml>
